<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Fiction">Fiction</span></h1>
<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reamde">Reamde</a> by <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neal_Stephenson">Neal Stephenson</a>. Key element of novel is a fictional <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MMORPG">MMORPG</a>.  Topics covered include <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gold_farming">goldfarming</a>.</li>
<li>Bruce Sterling's <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.lightspeedmagazine.com/fiction/maneki-neko/">Maneki Neko</a> (short story) - What if the net knew what you liked... and what you hated? What if everyone were given small tasks (quests, even) that promoted good behavior and discouraged bad behavior?</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://vimeo.com/46304267">Sight</a> short film depicting a future world where augmented reality and gaming collide.</li>
</ul>
<h1> <span class="mw-headline" id="Reads">Reads</span></h1>
<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.diigo.com/list/bowdenartist/gamification">Karen's List of Gamification Links</a> You can subscribe via RSS to my list on Diigo to receive an update each time I add new items.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://gigaom.com/2012/09/02/when-did-addiction-become-a-good-thing/">When Did Addiction Become A Good Thing?</a> Jason Hreha essay on GigaOM questioning "the ethics of manufacturing desire"</li>
<li>Good overview of the gamification from the .net Magazine <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.netmagazine.com/features/pro-s-guide-gamification">The pro's guide to gamification</a></li>
<li>Gamification blog by Kevin Werbach &amp; Dan Hunter <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://gamifyforthewin.com">www.gamifyforthewin.com</a></li>
<li>Harnessing the Power of Feedback Loops By Thomas Goetz <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.wired.com/magazine/2011/06/ff_feedbackloop/all/1">www.wired.com</a></li>
<li>20 Best Blogs About Game-Based Learning - <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://blogs.msdn.com/b/ukfe/archive/2012/08/20/the-20-best-blogs-about-game-based-learning.aspx">An Overview</a> by Tim Bush</li>
<li>Using gamification in a smart city - <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://urban360.me/2012/08/24/if-urban-life-is-a-game-smart-cities-are-the-playgrounds-gamification-civic-rewards-and-crowd-sourcing-strategies-for-connected-and-savvy-cities/">Urban360</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.bottomlineperformance.com/games-for-change-part-1-the-power-of-urgent-optimism-in-learning-games/">Games for Change Part 1</a> from Bottom-Line Performance by Steve Boller.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://center4edupunx.org/">Center4Edupunx</a> Bootstrapping Our Way Across the Curriculum blog.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://learnos.wordpress.com/2012/08/22/moocology/">MOOCology</a> by Viplav Baxi.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=1378704.1378719">Designing Games with a Purpose</a> An academic paper on the subject. </li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.infosysblogs.com/bpm-eai/2012/02/enterprise_gamification_-_the.html">Enterprise Gamification The Next Big Paradigm</a> A short article around the oppurtunities for Service Providers. </li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://nanodome.wordpress.com/2011/09/06/reverse-gamification-and-the-future-of-everything/">Reverse Gamification and the future of everything</a> Some thoughts on 'forward' and 'reverse' gamification. </li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.onlineuniversities.com/blog/2011/12/instant-gratification-and-education-strange-bedfellows/">Instant Gratification and Education: Strange Bedfellows?</a> An article about gamification and education. </li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.knewton.com/gamification-education/">The Gamification of Education Infographic</a> Infographic about gamification and education. </li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://learningintandem.blogspot.ca/2012/05/shamification-of-gamification.html">Learning in Tandem: The Shamification of Gamification</a> "We shouldn’t be shaming people for embracing the concept of gamification; we should be educating people on what good game and gamification design looks like so that they can spot the bad design."</li>
<li>Why not gamify your workplace? (<a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.gamificationofwork.com">http://www.gamificationofwork.com</a>)</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.astd.org/Publications/Blogs/L-and-D-Blog/2012/04/Why-Games-Dont-Teach">Why Games Don't Teach</a> Match game features to learning outcomes.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.hideandseek.net/2010/10/06/cant-play-wont-play/">Can't Play Won't Play</a> interesting piece from Margaret Robertson on whether gamification is the right term: she defines pointsification as a subset.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://pinterest.com/bubbleequity/gamification/">Pintrest site on Gamification</a> a collection of articles on the subject on a Pintrest board.</li>
<li>Karl Kapp's article (June 2012) <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.astd.org/Publications/Magazines/TD/TD-Archive/2012/06/Games-Gamification-and-the-Quest-for-Learner-Engagement">Games, Gamification, and the Quest for Learner Engagement</a>
-Ashlee Vance Galactic Crack Bloomburg Businessweek <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2013-04-18/multiplayer-game-eve-online-cultivates-a-most-devoted-following">http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2013-04-18/multiplayer-game-eve-online-cultivates-a-most-devoted-following</a> CCP Games, Eve Online and  a staff economist to manage the game's economy</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.thegamesjournal.com/articles/WhatIsaGame.shtml">What is a Game? by Wolfgang Kramer</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.wired.com/wiredenterprise/2012/11/gamification-customer-service/">How ‘Gamification’ Can Make Your Customer Service Worse</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.backbonemag.com/Magazine/2013-11/archive/how-wearable-tech-may-keep-you-alive.aspx">How wearable tech may keep you alive a little longer</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.idc.com/getdoc.jsp?containerId=prUS24598214">Utilities Will Spend $65 Million on Gamified Applications in 2016 to Engage Consumers, According to IDC Energy Insights </a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2015/01/22/how-to-make-a-puzzle-game/">How to make a good Puzzle Game</a></li>
</ul>
